The paper discusses the evolution and advancement of SDN in the context of next-generation networks, which falls under the category of computer networks and internet (cs.NI). It also covers the functional architecture of SDN and its related technologies, which could be classified under systems and control (cs.SY) and cryptography and security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the standardization efforts being carried out by different organizations, which could be classified under distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) and information theory (cs.IT).
